The '''Furtive Flycatcher''' ('''''Ficedula disposita''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the [[Muscicapidae]] family.
It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to the [[Philippines]].

Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane]]s.
It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].
